OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1776445554
OL,3,CThe extraordinary claims Starmer is
OL,4,Casking the public to believe on
OL,5,CMandelson
OL,7,FThe PM makes several extraordinary
OL,8,Fclaims when he says he hasn't been
OL,9,Flying about the circumstances of Peter
OL,10,FMandelson's appointment as US
OL,11,Fambassador - claims that his chief
OL,12,Fsecretary Darren Jones insists are
OL,13,Ftrue.
OL,15,FFirstly, that no one told him till
OL,16,FTuesday night - and he had no other
OL,17,Fway of knowing - that UK Security
OL,18,FVetting had recommended Peter
OL,19,FMandelson should not be appointed US
OL,20,Fambassador.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,314,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31302
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1776445554
OL,3,CThe extraordinary claims Starmer is
OL,4,Casking the public to believe on
OL,5,CMandelson
OL,7,FSecondly, that when Starmer told MPs
OL,8,Frepeatedly that "due process" had been
OL,9,Ffollowed in Mandelson's appointment,
OL,10,Fand when he told journalists on camera
OL,11,Fin Hastings in February, that
OL,12,FMandelson had passed the vetting
OL,13,Fprocess, no one at the foreign office
OL,14,Fthought to tip him off that Olly
OL,15,FRobbins - the now sacked permanent
OL,16,Fsecretary at the foreign office - had
OL,17,Fover-ruled UK Security Vetting
OL,26,@pD@QOUpD@]O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,314,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31303
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1776445554
OL,3,CThe extraordinary claims Starmer is
OL,4,Casking the public to believe on
OL,5,CMandelson
OL,7,FRobbins had the powers to do this,
OL,8,Fthough Jones insists no one at the
OL,9,Fcentre of government was aware of
OL,10,Fthese powers. And we are being asked
OL,11,Fto believe that Robbins unilaterally
OL,12,Ftook this hugely controversial
OL,13,Fdecision without consulting or
OL,14,Finforming any minister - even though
OL,15,FMandelson's appointment was almost
OL,16,Funiquely a political one, not a normal
OL,17,FWhitehall one.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,314,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31304
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1776445554
OL,3,CThe extraordinary claims Starmer is
OL,4,Casking the public to believe on
OL,5,CMandelson
OL,7,FAnd finally, that the most material of
OL,8,Fall facts in the Mandelson debacle,
OL,9,Fthat security officials did not
OL,10,Fbelieve Mandelson was fit and proper
OL,11,Fto be US ambassador, was only brought
OL,12,Fto the PM's attention on Tuesday night
OL,13,F- even though the government promised
OL,14,FMPs in early February it would publish
OL,15,Fall documents relevant to Mandelson's
OL,16,Fappointment and has been combing the
OL,17,Ffiles for ten weeks to find them.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,314,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31305
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1776445554
OL,3,CThe extraordinary claims Starmer is
OL,4,Casking the public to believe on
OL,5,CMandelson
OL,7,FJones's argument is that this debacle
OL,8,Fis not a failure of the PM but a
OL,9,Ffailure of the state. But that is a
OL,10,Fdouble-edged sword, because opposition
OL,11,Fleaders can legitimately point to the
OL,12,FBritish tradition of ministers taking
OL,13,Fresponsibility for state failures as
OL,14,Fegregious as this one - and Starmer
OL,15,Fshould resign.
OL,17,FSubscribe free to our weekly
OL,18,Fnewsletter for exclusive and original
OL,19,Fcoverage from ITV News. Direct to your
OL,20,Finbox every Friday morning.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,314,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31306
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1776445554
OL,3,CThe extraordinary claims Starmer is
OL,4,Casking the public to believe on
OL,5,CMandelson
OL,7,FSo the stakes will be enormously high
OL,8,Fwhen Starmer goes to the Commons to
OL,9,Fexplain himself on Monday. Badenoch
OL,10,Fsays, quite properly, that he should
OL,11,Fhave done so on Wednesday, as soon as
OL,12,Fhe knew that he had misled MPs,
OL,13,Falbeit, says Jones, unintentionally.
OL,14,FBut the moment of truth is only
OL,15,Fdelayed.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
